{"questionId":"27714","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The time worked, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math>, in hours per week by employees of a large company is normally&nbsp;distributed with a mean of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>42</mn></math> and standard deviation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the probability that an employee selected at random works more than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn></math> hours&nbsp;per week.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not penalize for inclusion or non-inclusion of endpoints for probabilities using a normal distribution. For example, for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>55</mn><mo> </mo><menclose notation=\"left\"><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>40</mn></menclose></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>55</mn><mo> </mo><menclose notation=\"left\"><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>40</mn></menclose></mrow></mfenced></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>55</mn><mo> </mo><menclose notation=\"left\"><mi>T</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>40</mn></menclose></mrow></mfenced></math>, etc.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>recognising to find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>40</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>40</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>574136</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>40</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>574</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27714","referenceCode":"22N.2.SL.TZ0.9a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the probability that an employee selected at random works more than 40 hours per week.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}